THE CACAO.

With the vaynilla we must speakof the cacao, which is produced by a tree resembling an orange tree in its leaves, but larger, and having akind of crown on the top. It bears a fruit like large melonS, containing oily kernels, as big as almonds, and separated from one another by a white and very sweet skin, as by a kind of ¹ fence. The Peruvian IndianS, throwing away the kernels which they did not then know how to use in preparing chocolate, were accustomed to chew and suck the little skin only, which is sweeter than honey.
